{"type":"run_title","message":"Task: UI: SSE log scroll position should be stable","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:06:01.354149056Z"}
{"type":"step_started","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:06:01.354313848Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"The implementation is clean and correct. Here's a summary of the changes:","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987249482Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987319144Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Problem:** The `autoScroll` state variable was updated via a `scroll` event listener, creating a race condition. If a log event arrived between the user starting to scroll and the scroll event firing, the scroll position was yanked back to the bottom.","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987325626Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987346826Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Fix in `run_detail.html`:**","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987352126Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- Removed the `autoScroll` state variable and the `scroll` event listener","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987362145Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- `appendLogLine()` now checks the scroll position synchronously *before* appending content (using `savedScrollTop`)","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987372685Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- If the user was at the bottom (within 40px), it auto-scrolls to show new content","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987378265Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- If the user was scrolled up, it restores `savedScrollTop` after the DOM append as a defensive measure against browser reflow","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987383405Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987393985Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Test in `handler_test.go`:**","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987403333Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- Added `TestRunDetail_LogScrollStabilization` verifying the template contains the stable scroll pattern (`savedScrollTop`, inline bottom-check, position restore) and does NOT contain the race-prone `var autoScroll` pattern","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987408473Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:10:14.987414354Z"}
